    "attributes": {
        "action": "For a better society -Hate Crime -should be a Mandatory Curriculum in schools",
        "additional_details": "The root cause of hate crimes is ignorance.\r\nChildren spend time in schools, schools have potential  to make and shape aware citizens.\r\nParliament should pass the bill to make children education and awareness on such issues mandatory.\r\nUK government should put aside funds to create and implement an effective curriculum for school children. \r\n Ignorance  should be tackled by creating and implementing  effective curriculum with the help of educationists and police department. Resulting better future.",
        "background": "I am a British Asian, Scotland is my home, all of  my adult life I worked here, I volunteered for Oxfam, for mental health charities, and was a permanent member of church based charity SVDP.  I never differentiated myself until I was subjected to hate crime.",
